# Frontend Tools for News Aggregator
1. HTML

--> For structure

--> Create layout, news cards, navbar, search bar

2. CSS

--> For design

--> Flexbox, Grid, responsive UI

3. JavaScript

--> To fetch news from API

--> To display news dynamically

--> To update UI (search, filter)

4. News API (Any One)

--> NewsAPI

--> GNews

--> Mediastack

--> RSS Feeds


# Tools Needed (Frontend + Authentication)
1. HTML

--> Login form

--> Signup form

--> Input fields (email, password)

2. CSS

--> Form styling

--> Error message styling

--> Buttons, layout

3. JavaScript

--> Form validation

--> Show/Hide password

--> Send login/signup data to backend

--> Store user session (token) in localStorage




# Tools Needed for HISTORY Feature (Frontend Only)
1. JavaScript LocalStorage
- This is the simplest tool.
- Used to save:

--> which news the user clicked

--> reading history

--> last search


2. JSON

--> To store history data in structured format.

3. DOM Manipulation

--> To display history on a separate page:

--> Show titles

--> Show images

--> Show links


# Tools Needed for SEARCH ENGINE (Frontend)
1. HTML
--> Search input box
--> Search button

2. CSS
--> Style search bar
--> Responsive design

3. JavaScript
--> To make search work:
--> input.value
--> addEventListener("keyup")
--> fetch() call with query
--> Show results on screen


4. API (News Search)

- Your API must support search query:
- Use any one:
--> NewsAPI
--> GNews
--> Mediastack
--> RSS feeds


# Search Engine Enhancement Tools
5. Debounce
--> So API does not call on every key press.
--> Used in JS:
-setTimeout()
-clearTimeout()

6. Filtering
--> You can add:
--> category filter
--> date filter
--> source filter


7. Sorting (Optional)
-- Sort results by:
--> newest
--> oldest


8. Pagination / Infinite Scroll
--> To load more search results smoothly.

# Delete History Feature

1. HTML

--> A “Delete History” button

--> A separate history page or section

2. CSS

--> Styling for delete button

--> Warning message style (optional)

3. JavaScript DOM

--> Show confirmation message

--> Update UI when history is deleted





